#Obtain Data
library(magrittr)

  dplyr::select(
      -model,-processor_name,-discount, -ratings

  as.data.frame()

Removed the model type because the model will be associated with the brand of a laptop. In addition, the brand has less unique values, which will help with the data analysis process. The processor name was also removed for similar reasons as the name would be associated with the brand of processor. The discount was also removed since we are looking to predict the latest price; therefore, if we have the discount, then we are no longer predicting the latest price. The ratings will also be removed as it has a high correlation with the number of reviews, suggesting they might be multicollinearity.

# partition data
set.seed(1)  # set seed for reproducing the partition
idx <- caret::createDataPartition(laptop_data$latest_price, p=0.6, list=FALSE)
train.df <- laptop_data[idx, ]
holdout.df <- laptop_data[-idx, ]

# use lm() to run a linear regression of Price on all 11 predictors in the
# training set.
# use . after ~ to include all the remaining columns in train.df as predictors.
laptop.lm <- lm(
  formula =  latest_price ~.,
  data = train.df,
  na.action=na.exclude
)
#  use options() to ensure numbers are not displayed in scientific notation.
options(scipen = 999)
summary(laptop.lm)
